This paper is primarily focused on improving the performance of datacenter networks, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper specifically addresses the issue of tail latency in short flows, which is a common problem in datacenter networks (cs.DC). The proposed solution involves prioritizing packets based on their congestion history, which involves system-level optimization (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the use of ECN mechanism, which is a congestion control technique (cs.CR). Finally, the paper involves the use of priority queues, which is a common data structure in information theory (cs.IT).
